Famous Nollywood actress turned politician Funke Akindele, on Saturday, makes her first public appearance after her mother’s death. The mother of two was captured on her way to observe her civic duties alongside her crew. Funke Akindele, who has been on and off social media since her mother’s demise, was captured while observing her civic duties at her polling unit in Lagos alongside her crew. Sharing the video in a post on her Instagram page, the actress urged Nigerians to go out and perform their civic rights. She wrote: ”My vote will count. I just voted. God bless Nigeria. God bless us all.” Recall that the news of Funke’s mother’s demise was announced on February 7th in an official statement posted on Instagram by the actress’s sister, Olubunmi Akindele. Since the incident, Funke has not made any public appearances.